"This is a basic-display iGPU built into your CPU - it's there for video output and troubleshooting, not for compute. For AI restyle the CPU on the same chip is typically 3 to 5 times faster."="This is a basic-display iGPU built into your CPU - it's there for video output and troubleshooting, not for compute. For AI restyle the CPU on the same chip is typically 3 to 5 times faster."
"Estimated wall-clock for this restyle:"="Estimated wall-clock for this restyle:"
"   - CPU mode: 5 to 10 minutes"="   - CPU mode: 5 to 10 minutes"
"   - This iGPU: 20 to 35 minutes"="   - This iGPU: 20 to 35 minutes"
"You can switch back to the iGPU later from the GPU picker in AI Settings."="You can switch back to the iGPU later from the GPU picker in AI Settings."
"Integrated GPUs are significantly underpowered compared to discrete cards for AI workloads. Typical wall-clock times for a FLUX.2 restyle:"="Integrated GPUs are significantly underpowered compared to discrete cards for AI workloads. Typical wall-clock times for a FLUX.2 restyle:"
"   - Modern AMD Ryzen 8000G / 7040 (RDNA3 Radeon 780M): 3 to 6 minutes"="   - Modern AMD Ryzen 8000G / 7040 (RDNA3 Radeon 780M): 3 to 6 minutes"
"   - Intel Core Ultra (Arc-class integrated): 4 to 8 minutes"="   - Intel Core Ultra (Arc-class integrated): 4 to 8 minutes"
"   - AMD Ryzen 5000G / 4000G (Vega): 8 to 15 minutes"="   - AMD Ryzen 5000G / 4000G (Vega): 8 to 15 minutes"
"   - Intel Iris Xe (11th-13th gen): 10 to 20 minutes"="   - Intel Iris Xe (11th-13th gen): 10 to 20 minutes"
"   - Older APUs / pre-Iris-Xe Intel: 20 minutes or more"="   - Older APUs / pre-Iris-Xe Intel: 20 minutes or more"
"You can cancel anytime from the preview screen. For routine use a discrete GPU with 6 GB or more VRAM is strongly recommended."="You can cancel anytime from the preview screen. For routine use a discrete GPU with 6 GB or more VRAM is strongly recommended."
"Use CPU mode (recommended)"="Use CPU mode (recommended)"
